question: What is the official gene symbol of GCS1?
agent_answer:
The official gene symbol for "GCS1" can refer to different genes depending on the organism. Here are some of the entries for "GCS1":

1. In yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae), "GCS1" is the official symbol, with the identifier [SGD:S000002385](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/SGD:S000002385).
2. In fruit fly (Drosophila melanogaster), "GCS1" is also the official symbol, with the identifier [FB:FBgn0030289](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/FB:FBgn0030289).
3. In humans, "GCS1" is associated with the gene symbol "ADAP1" (ArfGAP with dual PH domains 1), with the identifier [HGNC:16486](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:16486).
4. Another human gene associated with "GCS1" is "MOGS" (Mannosyl-Oligosaccharide Glucosidase), with the identifier [HGNC:24862](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:24862).
5. In fission yeast (Schizosaccharomyces pombe), "gcs1" is the official symbol, with the identifier [PomBase:SPAC22F3.10c](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/PomBase:SPAC22F3.10c).
6. In rats, "Mogs" is associated with "GCS1", with the identifier [RGD:69240](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/RGD:69240).
7. In mice, "Mogs" is associated with "GCS1", with the identifier [MGI:1929872](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/MGI:1929872).
